		    <title class="- topic/title ">
			      <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">24.201</ph> Authority.</title>
		    <conbody class="- topic/body concept/conbody ">
			      <p id="d1595e13" class="- topic/p ">The Freedom of Information Act (<ph class="- topic/ph ">
					          <xref href="http://uscode.house.gov/browse.xhtml;jsessionid=114A3287C7B3359E597506A31FC855B3"
                     format="html"
                     scope="external"
                     class="- topic/xref ">5 U.S.C.552</xref>
				        </ph>, as amended) provides that information is to be made available to the public either by-</p>
			      <ol id="d1581e22" class="- topic/ol ">
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1595e26" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(a)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Publication in the <i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i ">Federal Register</i>;</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1595e38" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(b)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Providing an opportunity to read and copy records at convenient locations; or</p>
				        </li>
				        <li class="- topic/li ">
					          <p id="d1595e47" class="- topic/p ">
                  <ph props="autonumber" class="- topic/ph ">(c)</ph>
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
                  
						            Upon request, providing a copy of a reasonably described record.</p>
				        </li>
			      </ol>
		    </conbody>
